        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4c07",
          "text": "Life is stranger than fiction! Who would have thought that one day I would have a deep conversation with Dr. Timothy Leary’s former partner, the amazing Joanna Harcourt-Smith (here is her bio). Just before the winter solstice Joanna and I spent an hour talking to each other on her Future Primitive podcast.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 191,
              "href": "https://futureprimitive.org/joanna/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 188,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "61ce",
          "text": "“This book is about love and practicing the love of life.” Joanna started her interview by referring to Graham Leicester’s introduction to Designing Regenerative Cultures. Biophilia lies at the heart of the process of cocreating diverse regenerative cultures everywhere.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 135,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@designforsustainability/graham-leicester-introduces-designing-regenerative-cultures-4789f3631699",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 104,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 181,
              "href": "https://medium.com/age-of-awareness/the-passionate-love-of-life-and-of-all-that-is-alive-af18e142df94",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 172,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "149d",
          "text": "We went on to explore the way that our future is now in jeopardy and how we need to develop an attitude of being healers in service to life without any attachment to the outcomes of our work. This healing takes place in the NOW — right here. If we develop our ability to love life more deeply in every moment we can leverage the future potential of the present to heal our relationships with each other and the Earth. DCW: “It is consciousness shift first and the world will follow.” JHS: “Absolutely!”",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "1c76",
          "text": "Joanna referred to the individual and collective trauma we carry and how it might block us from changing our outdated modes of thinking that no longer serve. Somehow her questions elicited answers that surprised me as I heard myself respond. Maybe it is less about us saving the world or saving life, but life is saving us by now confronting us with mortality and extinction to the extent that we are undergoing a species level rite of passage.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "021b",
          "text": "DCW: “In understanding that everything is an intervention lies a paradoxical insight. On the one hand, it brings you into the humility that reminds us to be mindful of every thought, every word, every action, our way of being not just what we are doing, because all of it transforms the world.”",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 225,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 209,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "1158",
          "text": "DCW: “At the same time, somewhere in connecting with that humility generated by the uncertainty we face also comes the understanding that we are not just part of the world we are it … deeply connected with all of her. All of us have the power to change the future and the present patterns of this process that we are participating in and emerging out of. That creates a huge amount of power and audacity [as we commit to healing the Earth and her people]. So it is the paradox of humility and audacity that we are now called to [embrace] at this point in human history.”",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 181,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 172,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 216,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 184,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_9",
          "href": null,
          "name": "2e67",
          "text": "Joanna shared that she believes “that we are exquisitely improvisiong the future at every moment” and that for her life is improvisation and that gives life deep meaning. JHS: “A lot of this is about greater meaning. Attending to other species and changing culture is a matter of meaning, isn’t it?”",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_10",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4627",
          "text": "[…]",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_11",
          "href": null,
          "name": "cde5",
          "text": "We go on to address:",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_12",
          "href": null,
          "name": "59ae",
          "text": "the key question about human survival [why are we worth it?];",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_13",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b58a",
          "text": "connecting young people with the living practices of regeneration [inviting the Fridays for Future generation to join the reGeneration];",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_14",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4892",
          "text": "acting in urgent times with active hope and the knowledge that “we now have to do the impossible because the probable has become unthinkable”;",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_15",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3174",
          "text": "changing the underlying narrative of our culture [from focussing on separating to celebrating interbeing];",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_16",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3e21",
          "text": "feeling the identity with the deep mycelial connection [sacred plants as guides and healers that have been used by indigenous cultures as part of rites of passage and to seek guidance beyond the rational analytical mind];",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_17",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8afa",
          "text": "how we see informs what we see [the role of our state of consciousness and our organizing ideas in how “we bring forth a world];",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_18",
          "href": null,
          "name": "2ac5",
          "text": "coming together in planetary collaboration to transform our way of being;",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_19",
          "href": null,
          "name": "899d",
          "text": "[the deep practice of reconnecting and gaining insight by] sitting with a question in the wilderness.”",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "e193622ba76a_20",
          "href": null,
          "name": "120e",
          "text": "… Check it out! I very much enjoyed my conversation with Joanna. Maybe it was the Leary connection that even prompted me to share from my own learning through the use of sacred plant medicine?",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
